Liq Performance Benchmark

Hardware

- CPU: Intel(R) Core(TM) i3-5005U CPU @ 2.00GHz
- RAM: 8 GB
- OS: Zorin OS

Model

- Llama 3.2 3B
- Runtime: Ollama

Results

- First response time: 50.76 seconds
- Maximum Python memory usage: 40,584 KB (~40 MB)
- Total system RAM: 7.7 GiB
- RAM used during test: 5.4 GiB
- Available RAM during test: 2.2 GiB
- Swap usage: Minimal (3.9 GiB available)
- Works correctly on CPU.
- Suitable for development, but optimization is needed to improve response speed.

Notes

- Liq successfully runs locally on an HP laptop with 8 GB RAM.
- The first response is slower because the model loads and performs inference on the CPU.
- Future benchmarks will compare Llama 3.2 3B with Phi-3 Mini and other local models.
- Performance will be measured again after implementing optimizations such as reduced chat history, streaming responses, and model comparison.